<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870817-0088 </DOCNO><HL> Russ Berrie andamp; Co.</HL><DD> 08/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> RUSEARNINGS (ERN)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Russ Berrie andamp; Co., citing continued growth in the U.S., Canada and Europe, reported second-quarter earnings rose 35% and sales increased 23%.    The Oakland, N.J., maker of toys and trinkets also completed the acquisitions of Maine Line Co., a greeting-card company in Rockport, Maine, and Fluf N' Stuf Inc., a chain of gift stores based in Collegeville, Pa. Terms weren't disclosed.    Second-quarter profit advanced to $4.1 million, or 27 cents a share, from $3 million, or 21 cents a share, in the year-earlier period. Sales grew to $55.2 million from $45 million.    Six-month profit rose 30% to $13 million, or 87 cents a share. Sales climbed 24% to a record $122.8 million. </TEXT></DOC>